Generic single-database configuration.

init: alembic init <directory>

Initializes a new migration environment in the specified directory.

revision: alembic revision -m "message"Creates a new migration script. Use the --autogenerate flag to automatically detect changes by comparing your models to the current database.

upgrade: alembic upgrade <revision>Applies migrations to reach a specific version. Use head to upgrade to the latest version.

downgrade: alembic downgrade <revision>Reverts to a previous migration. Use -1 to roll back only the most recent change.